Frequently Asked Questions:

What will be the timeline and sequence of construction?

Once passed, the sequence of events will include:

Demo Newberry Elementary;

Relocate Laybourne Field and construct a new 5,000-seat stadium to house football, soccer & track;

Construct the 6-8 grade portion of the building;

Move all middle school students into THEIR brand-new portion of the facility;

Demo BMS;

Construct the 9-12 grade portion of the new facility complete with a new 1,400 seat performing arts center with a 200-seat black box theatre;

Move remaining students into THEIR brand-new facility!

It is important to note, the sequencing of these steps is based upon the footprint of the building on the site. The overall timeline will include 18-24 months of designing and 24-36 months of construction. We are anticipating the placement of all 6-12 students in the new facilities in approximately 60 months or 5 years.

It is also important to note, some steps of this project may be happening simultaneously.

