Periodically, we will attempt to address frequently asked questions primarily regarding the issue on the ballot in November. The first question is:

The District has not maintained current buildings, why do we think the schools will improve their record on new buildings?

• Current buildings are being maintained as necessary. Due to their age, repairs are frequent and expensive. For example:
o New parking lots at Price, Preston, Lincoln and Richardson;
o New roofs at Bolich, DeWitt, Silver Lake, and part of CFHS;
o New boilers at CFHS;
o HVAC in all buildings;
o Security throughout the district, both inside and outside;
o Kitchen equipment in all buildings.

• We will continue to address issues as they emerge in our existing buildings as funds permit.

• With new construction, 0.5 mills or approximately $385,000/year, based on current valuation in the District, is dedicated to a maintenance fund which will secure funds for future repairs of the facility.

